sentences: Berislav Klobučar (28 August 1924 – 13 June 2014) was a Croatian opera conductor.
He conducted the Vienna State Opera for more than four decades, and guest conductor at the Bayreuth Festival.
Born in Zagreb on 28 August 1924, Klobučar was a student of conductor Lovro von Matačić.
During his forty-year tenure at the Vienna State Opera that began in 1952, he conducted 53 operas in 1,133 performances.
Berislav Klobučar died in Vienna, Austria on 13 June 2014 at the age of 89.
2010 Grand Decoration of Honour in Silver for Services to the Republic of Austria
Klobučar was conductor at the Bayreuth Festival in 1964 and 1967–69.
